#  CLI library taxonomy update: 11th TypeScript/Node CLI library —
#  Luke Edwards's **mri** (lukeed/mri).  TypeScript-Node ecosystem
#  now has 11 documented CLI libraries — TYING WITH RUST AND GO at
#  the top of the cross-language taxonomy in a THREE-WAY TIE.  🎉
#  TypeScript-Node CATCHES UP — restoring three-way parity (Rust=11,
#  Go=11, TypeScript-Node=11).
#
#  mri (lukeed/mri) is Luke Edwards's MINIMAL JS ARG PARSER — designed
#  as a DROP-IN BUT 5x FASTER REPLACEMENT for minimist (substack's
#  classic).  mri exists because minimist parses 1.5M args/sec but
#  mri parses 8M args/sec (per lukeed's benchmark suite) by being
#  RUTHLESSLY MINIMAL: no `--no-flag` automatic negation, no `--key.
#  dotted.path` deep object expansion, no `--key=val,val2,val3`
#  comma-split, no `parse-numbers` auto-coercion (mri preserves
#  strings; caller does Number() casting).  Used by tailwindlabs/
#  tailwindcss (`@tailwindcss/cli` v4 binary uses mri in
#  `packages/@tailwindcss-cli/src/utils/args.ts`), vitejs/vite
#  (`create-vite` scaffolder uses mri), QwikDev/qwik (Qwik framework
